WEBVTT

00:15.970 --> 00:18.790
[phone buzzes]

00:18.990 --> 00:21.560
[birds call]

00:23.730 --> 00:27.520
[phone continues to buzz]

00:34.030 --> 00:35.950
[Pip whimpers]

00:37.700 --> 00:40.290
[scraping, clattering]

00:46.210 --> 00:47.840
[sighs]

00:53.590 --> 00:56.050
[exhales, inhales]

01:04.480 --> 01:05.480
[metal clanks]

01:08.560 --> 01:11.470
[whispers] Pip...

01:11.670 --> 01:12.740
Hey.

01:15.740 --> 01:18.350
- [loud knocking]
- [gasps]

01:18.550 --> 01:21.450
[barks]

01:25.830 --> 01:27.070
[barks]

01:27.270 --> 01:28.170
[metal scrapes]

01:30.340 --> 01:32.740
- [Knocking]
- [Lulu] Alice?

01:32.940 --> 01:34.420
Alice it's me!

01:39.430 --> 01:41.330
[Lulu] Oh, my God.

01:41.530 --> 01:44.130
We... We had a fight.
You know, he got mad and...

01:44.330 --> 01:45.210
- What?
- I just...

01:45.410 --> 01:47.460
I just need to call him, you know?

01:47.660 --> 01:49.630
What happened?

01:49.830 --> 01:50.920
- [phone beeps]
- No, no...

01:51.120 --> 01:53.260
No, no, it's like... It... [stammers]

01:53.460 --> 01:54.930
[recording]
Hi, you've got Dylan...

01:55.130 --> 01:57.300
- Fuck, his phone's off.
- No, no, you don't need to call him.

01:57.500 --> 01:58.640
You don't understand, you know...

01:58.840 --> 02:00.470
He saw Aiden give me a hug
and he got mad.

02:00.670 --> 02:01.770
- He just told me...
- A hug?

02:01.970 --> 02:03.640
Yeah, he just saw me give him a hug

02:03.840 --> 02:07.110
and I just don't think he un...
understood kind of what was going on.

02:07.310 --> 02:09.860
I just, you know...
If I can just explain it to him...

02:10.060 --> 02:11.380
What are you...

02:14.460 --> 02:16.220
What are you doing?

02:17.720 --> 02:20.970
I need you to see yourself.

02:33.230 --> 02:35.230
[shower runs]

02:48.870 --> 02:50.790
[Lulu] You need to report it.

02:55.840 --> 02:57.360
What's going to happen if you don't?

02:57.560 --> 03:00.530
You... You take some sick days,

03:00.730 --> 03:04.310
try to cover up your bruises,
act like nothing's happened?

03:06.970 --> 03:10.540
And then what?
You have to keep working with him.

03:10.740 --> 03:12.730
And then he just gets away with it?

03:17.780 --> 03:19.610
[whispers] Did he ever...

03:21.070 --> 03:22.490
...hit you?

03:25.910 --> 03:27.850
He could be...

03:28.050 --> 03:30.360
cruel...

03:30.560 --> 03:32.040
jealous.

03:33.710 --> 03:36.590
He scared the shit out of me
a couple of times, but...

03:37.670 --> 03:39.800
...he was never in love with me.

03:44.350 --> 03:46.850
♪ ♪

03:47.890 --> 03:49.850
Can you help get these off?

04:17.460 --> 04:18.840
[grunts softly]

04:45.820 --> 04:47.280
[laughs]

04:49.030 --> 04:52.040
[both cry]

05:18.900 --> 05:20.150
[exhales]

05:24.900 --> 05:26.950
You look different.

05:29.870 --> 05:31.410
Well, I...

05:33.700 --> 05:35.730
...went looking for Alice
out in the desert

05:35.930 --> 05:38.730
and ended up out on country
with all the aunties.

05:38.930 --> 05:40.710
It was amazing.

05:46.380 --> 05:48.620
I got a message from Alice.

05:48.820 --> 05:51.580
And she said she wasn't ready to talk.

05:51.780 --> 05:53.000
But she's fine.

05:53.200 --> 05:55.230
She's happy, in love.

05:57.190 --> 05:58.650
Thank you.

06:05.490 --> 06:06.900
[door opens]

06:13.910 --> 06:15.770
Um... Thanks for seeing me...

06:15.970 --> 06:17.270
Yeah, look,
just before you say anything,

06:17.470 --> 06:20.670
I just want you to be aware that, uh,
Dylan's been in to see me...

06:21.960 --> 06:25.880
...and he's made some very serious
allegations against you.

06:29.930 --> 06:30.910
Against me?

06:31.110 --> 06:33.500
Yeah, he's saying that
the relationship that you were in,

06:33.700 --> 06:35.420
it's become toxic

06:35.620 --> 06:39.840
and he claims that you were
both verbally and physically abusive

06:40.040 --> 06:42.820
and that last night
you violently attacked him.

06:45.400 --> 06:47.530
No, he assaulted me.

06:49.110 --> 06:51.350
I can see that you're hurt, but, um,

06:51.550 --> 06:54.310
well, Dylan, he's got cuts and bruises
go all over his...

06:54.510 --> 06:56.190
Yeah, 'cause I was defending myself.

06:56.390 --> 06:58.040
I mean, he was...

06:59.670 --> 07:01.670
He was going to kill me.

07:05.960 --> 07:09.030
Dylan is also claiming, um...

07:09.230 --> 07:11.040
Alice, I do have to ask you this,
I'm sorry.

07:11.240 --> 07:13.410
But he's also claiming that...

07:13.610 --> 07:17.080
[becomes distant] ...you lied to me
about your qualifications,

07:17.280 --> 07:19.890
about your degree, just to get this job.

07:21.190 --> 07:24.130
And he's also saying that...

07:24.330 --> 07:26.760
that you've got a violent history,

07:26.960 --> 07:29.180
dating back to when you were a kid.

07:29.380 --> 07:31.560
And he also mentioned a fire.

07:31.760 --> 07:34.730
And these are
very serious allegations.

07:34.930 --> 07:38.330
- So I really...
- [laughs]

07:44.040 --> 07:45.780
Alice, I...

07:45.980 --> 07:47.920
I really don't think this is funny.

07:48.960 --> 07:51.580
You know, Dylan, he is one of
our most senior rangers

07:51.780 --> 07:55.700
and we have never had any problem,
not in four years.

07:55.900 --> 07:58.870
But, um, today I...

07:59.070 --> 08:00.810
I've never seen him so upset.

08:06.230 --> 08:08.630
These are up all over Agnes Bluff.

08:08.830 --> 08:11.930
Now, I have to suspend you from duties,
pending a formal inquiry.

08:12.130 --> 08:14.850
[becomes distant] That means HR from
Canberra...

08:15.050 --> 08:17.490
♪ ♪

08:23.830 --> 08:25.830
[Lulu] I can't believe she said that.

08:28.300 --> 08:29.950
Nah, fuck her.

08:30.150 --> 08:31.410
And fuck the sunset circus.

08:31.610 --> 08:33.580
Someone else can take my tour.
I'm taking you to the police.

08:33.780 --> 08:35.760
No, don't get in trouble on my account.

08:39.310 --> 08:41.420
I'll go after. It's OK.

08:41.620 --> 08:43.480
You can't stay here, though.

08:45.020 --> 08:46.020
[Ruby] Hey.

08:49.070 --> 08:51.800
Come on.
You're coming with me on the tour.

08:52.000 --> 08:53.950
I'll look after you, OK?

08:55.700 --> 08:57.990
[birds call]

09:05.670 --> 09:08.380
[indistinct chatter]

09:32.280 --> 09:35.050
Hey, what are you doing?

09:35.250 --> 09:36.390
Why don't you mind your business?

09:36.590 --> 09:39.660
It clearly says don't take the flowers!

09:40.780 --> 09:42.230
- Stop!
- Jesus!

09:42.430 --> 09:43.770
Alice, what are you doing?

09:43.970 --> 09:45.940
What are you doing?

09:46.140 --> 09:49.940
- [woman] Somebody help me, please!
- [Lulu] Alice, stop!

09:50.140 --> 09:52.280
Alice! Alice, get off her!

09:52.480 --> 09:55.340
[both breathe heavily]

10:22.240 --> 10:24.750
[pants]

10:34.710 --> 10:37.470
[men talk indistinctly]

10:38.550 --> 10:41.930
[Thugger] Who knew Alice was
such a crazy fucking bitch?

10:43.810 --> 10:45.520
Did you see this?

10:47.060 --> 10:49.840
[indistinct shouting on recording]

10:50.040 --> 10:51.960
- I told you she was fucking crazy.
- [woman]
Somebody help me...

10:52.160 --> 10:54.550
- [recording continues]
- She does this to a tourist?

10:54.750 --> 10:56.320
[Ruby, on recording]
Alice, get off her!

10:58.150 --> 10:59.640
[Sniffs]

10:59.840 --> 11:01.220
It's going to be alright, mate.

11:01.420 --> 11:03.640
Knack for trouble, eh?

11:03.840 --> 11:05.770
Let's have a look at you. Come on.

11:05.970 --> 11:08.360
Got to be one headache, I reckon, that.

11:08.560 --> 11:10.940
Jesus. Who's got the beers?

11:11.140 --> 11:13.190
[indistinct chatter]

11:13.390 --> 11:14.840
[man] Get one for me.

11:23.050 --> 11:26.390
[breathes deeply]

11:35.020 --> 11:37.380
[dials phone]

11:37.580 --> 11:39.440
[phone rings]

11:44.370 --> 11:47.740
Alice. Alice?

11:52.120 --> 11:53.670
Alice.

11:55.340 --> 11:58.780
[sniffles] I need to come home.

11:58.980 --> 12:00.510
Darling girl...

12:02.130 --> 12:04.540
What is it, sweetheart?

12:04.740 --> 12:06.850
- What's happened?
- [sniffles]

12:08.600 --> 12:10.100
[sighs]

12:11.310 --> 12:15.440
[sobs] I... I need you to come get me.

12:20.400 --> 12:22.700
I need to come home.

12:26.160 --> 12:29.620
[sobs]
I don't...
I don't want to be here.

12:31.250 --> 12:33.610
[sobs]

12:33.810 --> 12:35.130
I'm here.

12:36.960 --> 12:38.590
I'm here.

12:41.590 --> 12:42.970
I'm here.

12:44.720 --> 12:47.260
[birds call]

13:03.820 --> 13:07.870
Now I get to go back to Thornfield,
another fucked-up flower.

13:16.170 --> 13:17.670
[whispers] Not so.

13:23.470 --> 13:25.010
Not so.

13:26.340 --> 13:29.390
♪ ♪

13:45.780 --> 13:48.740
[breathes shakily]

13:52.990 --> 13:55.160
[cries]

14:09.590 --> 14:10.790
[dials]

14:10.990 --> 14:12.560
Sally.

14:14.430 --> 14:15.980
Um, it's June.

14:17.980 --> 14:21.260
I'm, uh, calling to...

14:21.460 --> 14:23.590
♪ ♪

14:23.790 --> 14:26.110
[June continues indistinctly]

14:43.250 --> 14:45.050
[pants softly]

15:03.980 --> 15:05.320
[Gasps]

15:10.860 --> 15:14.080
[waves roll on the beach]

15:46.730 --> 15:48.470
[Alice] Why are we here?

15:48.670 --> 15:50.220
[June] A long time ago, I...

15:50.420 --> 15:53.490
I lied to you
about something very important.

15:58.950 --> 16:02.190
Your brother didn't die in the fire.

16:02.390 --> 16:04.440
Your mother went into labour,

16:04.640 --> 16:08.700
and he was born much too soon
and very sick.

16:08.900 --> 16:10.070
- And they took him to Sydney...
- What?

16:10.270 --> 16:13.540
...to try to save him,
and eventually they did.

16:13.740 --> 16:18.080
I gave him up for adoption
to Sally Morgan.

16:18.280 --> 16:23.940
She's the librarian who
took care of you in the hospital here.

16:29.320 --> 16:30.900
[stammers]

16:33.030 --> 16:35.060
I have... I have a brother?

16:35.260 --> 16:38.240
[June] You have a wonderful brother.

16:39.450 --> 16:42.830
And I'm so sorry I kept you apart.

16:45.330 --> 16:46.790
You see...

16:55.510 --> 16:58.750
Are you fucking kidding me?

16:58.950 --> 17:01.170
No.

17:01.370 --> 17:04.210
Agh...! [screams] You are not...!

17:04.410 --> 17:05.310
Fuck!

17:11.610 --> 17:13.490
Do you want me to go after her?

17:20.370 --> 17:22.450
No, just watch her.

17:25.080 --> 17:26.370
[sighs]

17:31.130 --> 17:34.620
♪ ♪

17:34.820 --> 17:37.220
[indistinct chatter]

17:39.930 --> 17:42.310
[woman] Like a little alleyway
crossing this way.

17:46.350 --> 17:49.810
- [birds call]
- [indistinct chatter]

18:35.860 --> 18:37.570
Looking for this?

18:54.630 --> 18:56.260
What's he like?

18:59.340 --> 19:01.300
He's kind of hard to sum up.

19:02.720 --> 19:05.470
Probably better to let Charlie
speak for himself.

19:06.720 --> 19:09.060
He's so excited to meet you.

19:11.480 --> 19:15.610
He's... He's waited a long time
for this day.

19:18.190 --> 19:20.570
- He knows about me?
- Of course.

19:22.240 --> 19:24.350
He's always known about you, Alice,

19:24.550 --> 19:26.490
his big, beautiful sister.

19:29.960 --> 19:31.540
I'm...

19:32.630 --> 19:35.750
I'm a bit of a mess, hey?
I don't know that I'm...

19:37.590 --> 19:39.510
I'm not quite ready.

19:42.640 --> 19:46.430
How about I just make us a nice
cup of tea? We can eat some cake.

19:48.270 --> 19:50.270
I made you lamingtons.

19:53.730 --> 19:56.020
You knew I was coming?

19:58.900 --> 20:00.570
June.

20:06.490 --> 20:09.870
[boys chat and laugh]

20:17.210 --> 20:19.910
- Hey, Twig.
- Hey, Charlie.

20:20.110 --> 20:22.370
- I'll leave these for Alice.
- OK.

20:22.570 --> 20:25.160
- Thank you.
- That's alright.

20:25.360 --> 20:28.010
Give us a hug, bub. Hey.

20:34.100 --> 20:36.940
- See you.
- Bye, Twig.

20:40.990 --> 20:44.030
[boys continue laughing and chatting]

20:46.820 --> 20:48.120
[exhales]

20:53.330 --> 20:55.830
Where to? Home?

21:02.420 --> 21:04.090
Come on.

21:05.390 --> 21:07.140
Watch your step.

21:09.680 --> 21:11.420
Don't you go dying on me, woman.

21:11.620 --> 21:13.690
I've got to get you
up these bloody steps.

21:21.780 --> 21:23.360
Trapped...

21:30.240 --> 21:32.080
Want to go home...

21:40.500 --> 21:42.300
Children...

21:47.050 --> 21:48.890
Escape...

21:55.640 --> 21:57.310
Returned to...

21:58.560 --> 22:00.110
...her sisters...

22:02.110 --> 22:03.740
What the hell is this?

22:12.160 --> 22:16.370
It was the only way we could communicate
without Clem knowing.

22:19.500 --> 22:21.000
He kept...

22:22.170 --> 22:24.420
He kept a close eye on your mum.

22:28.840 --> 22:32.010
So you sent messages through books?

22:36.020 --> 22:37.600
You were friends?

22:41.060 --> 22:43.800
I wanted to help her.

22:44.000 --> 22:46.240
She was trying to leave your dad...

22:47.900 --> 22:51.100
...take you away to somewhere safe,

22:51.300 --> 22:53.060
you and Charlie.

22:53.260 --> 22:57.560
Was she going to go, or was it just talk
and more fucking fairytales?

22:57.760 --> 23:01.570
No. She had a definite plan.

23:01.770 --> 23:04.320
She knew where she wanted to take you.

23:04.520 --> 23:06.010
It's all in here.

23:15.930 --> 23:19.770
I only realised when I went
to Thornfield and I saw the sign.

23:21.810 --> 23:25.070
You ended up exactly where
your mum wanted you to be.

23:32.870 --> 23:35.080
So it is all my... my fault?

23:36.700 --> 23:38.770
No, Alice.

23:38.970 --> 23:43.110
- I fucked the plan. I fucked the plan.
- No.

23:43.310 --> 23:47.490
[sobs] I fucked the plan,
with the... with the fire and...

23:47.690 --> 23:50.370
I fucked the... [sobs]

23:50.570 --> 23:53.080
No, no, no. This is...
This is not your fault.

23:53.280 --> 23:55.330
I...

23:55.530 --> 23:58.750
With the fire in the shed,
I didn't... I didn't mean to kill them.

23:58.950 --> 23:59.920
I... I didn't...

24:00.120 --> 24:01.790
Alice, there's something
you need to see.

24:01.990 --> 24:04.010
Trust me, it's not your fault.

24:04.210 --> 24:06.230
I didn't know the plan...

24:08.110 --> 24:10.070
♪ ♪

24:16.830 --> 24:19.370
[inaudible]

24:24.460 --> 24:26.040
It's OK.

24:41.230 --> 24:44.800
"An inquest is not designed
to apportion blame.

24:45.000 --> 24:48.010
It's an inquisitorial process.

24:48.210 --> 24:51.590
"The aim is to obtain a full
and frank account of what happened

24:51.790 --> 24:55.180
"in the lead-up to
Agnes and Clem Hart's deaths,

24:55.380 --> 24:58.270
"and determine whether
lessons have been learnt

24:58.470 --> 25:01.040
"so that lives can be saved
in the future.

25:02.460 --> 25:06.110
"At the time of inquest,
Alice Hart was unable to be interviewed,

25:06.310 --> 25:09.670
"as she was still recovering
from her injuries in hospital.

25:12.220 --> 25:14.200
"The sustained assault by her father

25:14.400 --> 25:17.120
"resulted in broken bones,
collapsed lung,

25:17.320 --> 25:20.460
"head and neck trauma.

25:20.660 --> 25:24.310
"Alice Hart has not spoken
since the day of the fire.

25:27.560 --> 25:29.800
"Agnes Hart lived in fear for her life

25:30.000 --> 25:33.190
"and the lives of her daughter Alice
and her unborn son.

25:34.320 --> 25:36.220
"Her husband, Clem Hart,

25:36.420 --> 25:40.410
"was both a committed partner
and also deeply controlling.

25:47.580 --> 25:51.860
"Despite these impediments,
Agnes befriended librarian Sally Morgan

25:52.060 --> 25:57.200
"and made plans to leave Clem
and take her to a refuge known to her,

25:57.400 --> 25:59.760
"somewhere she believed they'd be safe.

26:02.060 --> 26:05.590
"On 7 January 2007,

26:05.790 --> 26:10.170
"Agnes attended her pre-natal check-up
at the Wyuna Base Hospital,

26:10.370 --> 26:11.340
"accompanied by Clem."

26:11.540 --> 26:14.690
We'll pick you up some more books
from the library if we have time.

26:16.280 --> 26:17.850
Can we keep the Selkie story?

26:18.050 --> 26:19.570
We've already read that.

26:20.830 --> 26:23.700
OK, please try to be good.

26:31.920 --> 26:35.570
"After the hospital,
they visited the local library,

26:35.770 --> 26:37.910
"where Agnes updated
librarian Sally Morgan

26:38.110 --> 26:39.740
"of her plan to leave Clem,

26:39.940 --> 26:42.390
"the message contained in a book."

26:47.480 --> 26:50.170
"Agnes then returned home with Clem.

26:50.370 --> 26:52.510
"From forensic reports,

26:52.710 --> 26:54.840
a small fire had broken out
in the shed."

26:55.040 --> 26:56.940
[barking]

27:03.660 --> 27:05.140
[Clem] Alice!

27:05.340 --> 27:07.230
[Agnes] Alice!

27:07.430 --> 27:09.440
- Clem...
- [shouts] Alice!

27:09.640 --> 27:12.240
[Agnes] Clem! Please, Clem!

27:12.440 --> 27:14.130
Clem, please!

27:15.840 --> 27:18.870
Please don't hurt her, Clem!

27:19.070 --> 27:20.800
[gasps]

27:23.760 --> 27:25.410
Alice!

27:25.610 --> 27:26.890
[Agnes] Clem!

27:29.140 --> 27:30.960
- Alice!
- Clem!

27:31.160 --> 27:32.630
[barking]

27:32.830 --> 27:34.260
[screams] Clem!

27:34.460 --> 27:36.630
Clem, stop it!

27:36.830 --> 27:40.140
Clem, stop it! Please!

27:40.340 --> 27:42.450
[barking continues]

27:43.870 --> 27:45.690
[Alice gasps]

27:45.890 --> 27:49.900
[Agnes shouts] Stop it! Clem!

27:50.100 --> 27:52.630
[Alice gasps and chokes]

27:56.380 --> 27:58.010
[screams]

28:00.260 --> 28:02.180
[Alice struggles to breathe]

28:26.830 --> 28:29.730
[Alice reads]
"Agnes then left the house
and returned to Alice,

28:29.930 --> 28:31.870
"going into early labour.

28:35.500 --> 28:39.030
"First responders found her
suffering from severe smoke inhalation

28:39.230 --> 28:41.050
"and in distress.

28:44.010 --> 28:46.200
"It is the finding of this inquiry

28:46.400 --> 28:49.540
"that Agnes Mary Hart...
killed Clem Hart

28:49.740 --> 28:55.050
"to save her daughter's life
as she was attacked by her father,

28:55.250 --> 28:58.670
"her final actions
borne out of years of violence and abuse

28:58.870 --> 29:00.840
"at the hands of her husband."

29:01.040 --> 29:04.320
[breathes heavily]

30:01.130 --> 30:04.340
♪ ♪

31:05.360 --> 31:08.820
[♪ "O Waly, Waly" plays]

31:16.370 --> 31:18.400
[Twig] How's Alice?

31:18.600 --> 31:21.860
[Sally]
Uh, better, I think.
Still processing.

31:22.060 --> 31:24.990
I spoke to her about Clem and Gemma.

31:25.190 --> 31:27.010
How did that all play out?

31:28.630 --> 31:31.260
Well, it was fine.

31:33.350 --> 31:36.180
She and Charlie
are making up for lost time.

31:37.390 --> 31:39.040
How's June doing?

31:39.240 --> 31:41.150
She's still here.

31:42.350 --> 31:43.860
Still sleeping.

31:45.190 --> 31:47.230
I think she can here hear us.

31:48.740 --> 31:52.350
We've loved hearing Charlie's messages.

31:52.550 --> 31:54.770
But if you could get Alice
to give us a call,

31:54.970 --> 31:57.790
I know June
would love to hear her voice.

31:59.080 --> 32:02.860
I can't promise anything, Twig,
but I will try again.

32:03.060 --> 32:04.030
Speak soon.

32:04.230 --> 32:06.900
[Nurse] Keep up the fluids.
Don't worry about food anymore.

32:07.100 --> 32:11.530
It's just about keeping her comfortable
at this stage.

32:11.730 --> 32:13.330
Thank you.

32:13.530 --> 32:15.220
Come on.

32:19.810 --> 32:22.140
Boo, you're up.

32:28.030 --> 32:30.840
I know you prefer poker,

32:31.040 --> 32:32.930
but we're playing patience.

32:33.130 --> 32:34.770
No cheating.

32:34.970 --> 32:36.410
I know what you're like.

32:40.160 --> 32:43.710
[♪ "O Waly, Waly" continues]

33:03.440 --> 33:04.980
What about Clem?

33:07.020 --> 33:10.090
Do I look like him a bit or...?

33:10.290 --> 33:12.240
I kinda hate that idea.

33:13.650 --> 33:15.450
You do look like him a little bit.

33:17.660 --> 33:19.770
But it's...

33:19.970 --> 33:22.560
It's not a bad thing.

33:22.760 --> 33:25.900
'Cause he wasn't all bad, you know?

33:26.100 --> 33:28.190
There was good too.

33:28.390 --> 33:30.670
He was artistic and strong.

33:34.970 --> 33:38.180
But, you know, just when you were
feeling safe and happy...

33:39.470 --> 33:41.060
...he'd turn...

33:42.680 --> 33:45.140
...as if some invisible slight or...

33:49.150 --> 33:51.840
Are you ever going to charge him?

33:52.040 --> 33:53.530
With assault?

33:55.820 --> 33:57.240
Dylan.

34:01.700 --> 34:03.750
Aren't you going to be late for school?

34:19.600 --> 34:21.460
Hi.

34:21.660 --> 34:23.500
Not to pile on too much pressure,

34:23.700 --> 34:27.020
but... Twig called this morning.

34:28.650 --> 34:31.110
June's not doing well.

34:33.110 --> 34:35.070
They'd love it if you gave them a call.

34:36.530 --> 34:38.390
Or even left a message for her.

34:38.590 --> 34:40.310
What do I say in that message?

34:40.510 --> 34:44.790
"Thank you so much for telling me
my brother was dead the last 14 years?"

34:50.920 --> 34:54.380
[♪ Sycco: "Germs"]

35:12.980 --> 35:14.400
[phone dings]

35:16.860 --> 35:19.610
[♪ Sycco: "Germs"]

36:08.950 --> 36:12.000
[Twig] You always said
honey could cure anything.

36:42.950 --> 36:44.780
Um...

36:56.130 --> 36:59.630
♪ ♪

37:06.010 --> 37:08.250
[Clem]
We're going to get married
at Thornfield

37:08.450 --> 37:11.080
and then afterwards get a place
of our own.

37:11.280 --> 37:13.630
But we wouldn't go far.

37:13.830 --> 37:16.810
I couldn't imagine
living without you guys.

37:18.150 --> 37:23.800
Well, actually, I was thinking
I could build a us a cottage.

37:24.000 --> 37:25.510
Here.

37:25.710 --> 37:27.770
Down by the river.

37:27.970 --> 37:29.230
[Agnes] Really?

37:29.430 --> 37:31.770
Yeah.

37:31.970 --> 37:34.400
Thornfield has been rundown for so long.

37:34.600 --> 37:36.020
The whole place needs to be modernised.

37:36.220 --> 37:38.360
There's so much land here.
There's so much...

37:38.560 --> 37:40.450
so much opportunity.

37:40.650 --> 37:42.870
Maybe we could even renovate this place.

37:43.070 --> 37:45.120
Just think about what it could become.

37:45.320 --> 37:47.910
Clem, I would like to see you privately.

37:48.110 --> 37:49.810
Now.

37:56.020 --> 38:00.300
You will not be building anything
at Thornfield because it is not yours,

38:00.500 --> 38:02.130
and never will be.

38:02.330 --> 38:03.930
Why are you saying that?

38:04.130 --> 38:05.930
You know why.

38:06.130 --> 38:10.140
When I die, Thornfield goes to Twig
and your sister Candy.

38:10.340 --> 38:11.890
Not you.

38:12.090 --> 38:14.150
The Candy stuff, it's nothing.

38:14.350 --> 38:16.190
Well, if it's nothing,

38:16.390 --> 38:19.920
you won't mind me telling Agnes that
you raped your little sister.

38:27.720 --> 38:29.330
- [shouts]
- Agh!

38:29.530 --> 38:32.600
[June groans and gasps]

38:37.730 --> 38:40.170
You won't tell her a thing.

38:40.370 --> 38:41.840
Not a word.

38:42.040 --> 38:44.590
[June gasps]

38:44.790 --> 38:47.100
Clem! Get off her!

38:47.300 --> 38:48.430
[June gasps]

38:48.630 --> 38:51.390
- Get out of here!
- [coughs]

38:51.590 --> 38:54.440
- [Clem] Agnes!
- [coughs]

38:54.640 --> 38:56.310
[Clem] Agnes!

38:56.510 --> 38:59.610
[June coughs] D... Don't...
Don't let him take Agnes!

38:59.810 --> 39:01.250
[coughs]

39:09.180 --> 39:11.850
[wind chimes tinkle]

39:17.180 --> 39:19.270
[Agnes] It had to be this way...

39:21.150 --> 39:22.380
...for Alice.

39:22.580 --> 39:23.860
[Twig] June.

39:32.410 --> 39:34.990
Come on. [grunts]

39:47.380 --> 39:49.300
You need anything else?

39:50.720 --> 39:54.120
I'm finishing this for Alice.

39:54.320 --> 39:55.560
OK.

40:19.500 --> 40:21.870
♪ ♪

40:24.790 --> 40:26.880
[whimpers]

40:28.460 --> 40:31.880
[♪ The Triffids: "Bury Me Deep In Love"]

40:34.930 --> 40:36.510
[knocks]

40:38.310 --> 40:40.060
[Sally] Hi.

40:41.100 --> 40:43.020
Alice, I don't want to intrude.

40:44.690 --> 40:48.730
I don't think you should be...
sucked back into Dylan.

40:50.320 --> 40:52.180
And that stuff is dangerous.

40:52.380 --> 40:54.280
Can make you crazy.

40:55.870 --> 40:57.680
There are ways of blocking that.
I can help...

40:57.880 --> 41:00.750
Yeah, no, I... I... I know.

41:02.290 --> 41:04.830
Really, I'm not going back there.

41:10.800 --> 41:12.160
[door closes]

41:12.360 --> 41:15.220
[ song continues]

41:28.860 --> 41:31.610
[phone buzzes]

41:46.370 --> 41:48.690
[bees buzz loudly]

41:48.890 --> 41:50.420
You hear that?

41:53.130 --> 41:54.760
They're swarming.

41:56.680 --> 41:58.140
The bees.

42:04.480 --> 42:07.060
♪ ♪

42:08.310 --> 42:10.270
[grunts softly]

42:17.610 --> 42:20.950
It means a new queen has been born.

42:24.290 --> 42:27.210
[bees buzz]

42:34.010 --> 42:36.580
I could murder a gin and tonic
and a bag of chips.

42:36.780 --> 42:39.800
I'll get you one. I'll get you one.
[chuckles]

42:42.680 --> 42:44.890
[breathes deeply]

43:02.200 --> 43:04.450
[inaudible]

43:07.750 --> 43:10.880
[♪ The Rolling Stones: "Gimme Shelter"]

43:58.550 --> 44:00.010
[inaudible]

44:18.820 --> 44:20.360
Chips?

44:31.710 --> 44:33.630
[music fades]

44:40.510 --> 44:42.970
Just a little bit.

44:54.400 --> 44:55.860
[exhales]

44:59.570 --> 45:02.320
[Lyrebird calls]

45:11.000 --> 45:13.540
[lyrebird continues]

45:31.640 --> 45:34.060
- One more for the road.
- Mmm.

45:38.310 --> 45:39.650
June?

45:43.450 --> 45:45.570
[faintly] June?

46:00.920 --> 46:04.050
[Birds chirping]

46:06.720 --> 46:09.350
♪ ♪

47:33.640 --> 47:35.290
[Candy] Hi.

47:35.490 --> 47:38.130
- I'm sorry.
- Oh! It's OK.

47:38.330 --> 47:39.750
It's OK.

47:39.950 --> 47:41.670
Oh, I've missed you.

47:41.870 --> 47:43.730
You're here now.

47:48.950 --> 47:51.100
Oh, my goodness.

47:51.300 --> 47:52.470
Charlie.

47:52.670 --> 47:55.310
[gasps] Charlie!
Oh, my goodness.

47:55.510 --> 47:57.190
Hello.

47:57.390 --> 47:58.910
So good to meet you.

48:00.040 --> 48:02.480
- You really do have the blue hair.
- I do.

48:02.680 --> 48:04.780
- Hi, I'm Candy.
- Sally.

48:04.980 --> 48:06.450
Sally, nice to meet you.
Hi. Candy.

48:06.650 --> 48:07.860
- John.
- John, nice to meet you.

48:08.060 --> 48:09.200
Welcome, welcome.

48:09.400 --> 48:11.830
- Oh, it's beautiful.
- Thank you.

48:12.030 --> 48:13.850
- Isn't it?
- Welcome to Thornfield.

48:14.890 --> 48:16.930
[chatter continues indistinctly]

48:23.560 --> 48:25.340
How many people are you expecting?

48:25.540 --> 48:26.970
Just us.

48:27.170 --> 48:29.070
And the flowers.

48:44.380 --> 48:46.690
My mother June would have hated this.

48:46.890 --> 48:49.660
- [All laugh]
- Yes, she would!

48:49.860 --> 48:53.200
She made it very clear
she wanted a simple send-off,

48:53.400 --> 48:56.500
no fuss, as few words as possible.

48:56.700 --> 48:59.470
Just family and flowers.

49:01.310 --> 49:04.840
Well, I kept my word.

49:05.040 --> 49:07.480
It is the flowers and their families,

49:09.110 --> 49:11.550
and look at how
you wildflowers have bloomed.

49:11.750 --> 49:14.530
[Applause and cheering]

49:16.530 --> 49:18.790
- We love you.
- [cheering continues]

49:21.080 --> 49:23.670
Can Charlie and Alice
come up here, please?

49:24.960 --> 49:27.210
[Applause and cheering]

49:41.430 --> 49:45.550
We all know Alice,
June's much-loved granddaughter.

49:45.750 --> 49:46.920
[Applause and cheering]

49:47.120 --> 49:48.860
Welcome back!

49:53.400 --> 49:55.410
And this is Charlie...

49:56.570 --> 49:58.390
...June's grandson.

49:58.590 --> 50:01.410
[Applause and cheering]

50:03.710 --> 50:07.360
They are the children
of June's son, Clem,

50:07.560 --> 50:10.360
and his lovely wife, Agnes,

50:10.560 --> 50:12.820
who are no longer with us.

50:13.020 --> 50:15.590
♪ ♪

50:23.390 --> 50:25.730
[cries softly]

50:31.150 --> 50:33.650
[both sob quietly]

50:59.970 --> 51:02.970
[sobs softly]

51:12.020 --> 51:13.650
We all got one.

51:45.640 --> 51:48.940
[June]
"My darling daughter...

51:51.480 --> 51:53.480
"What a gift you are..."

51:55.570 --> 51:57.780
[Sniffs]

52:05.490 --> 52:07.290
Oh...

52:15.250 --> 52:18.130
[lyrebird calls]

52:21.470 --> 52:23.800
[cries]

52:41.700 --> 52:44.240
[cries softly]

53:00.460 --> 53:02.240
[June]
"Dear Alice...

53:02.440 --> 53:06.660
"When we stay silent, they win.

53:06.860 --> 53:10.750
"In my shed there's a book
I've put aside for you

53:10.950 --> 53:14.060
"that I call 'The Lost Flowers'.

53:22.900 --> 53:25.430
"Alice, these are the stories
I should have shared with you

53:25.630 --> 53:29.990
"when you were old enough to hear them,
and still looking for answers.

53:38.710 --> 53:41.160
"When women started to come here,

53:41.360 --> 53:45.910
"it became almost a ritual that
one night they'd come to the shed

53:46.110 --> 53:51.720
"and tell me what had happened to them
and watch as I wrote it down.

53:55.730 --> 53:59.770
"A record, there in black and white.

54:10.330 --> 54:14.580
"They're the stories
I started to write as a young woman.

54:18.250 --> 54:21.860
"I had my voice taken from me
in a brutal crime at the river

54:22.060 --> 54:23.820
"when I was very young.

54:24.020 --> 54:26.880
"I let men silence me.

54:29.510 --> 54:35.430
"Writing down these stories,
I found my voice again.

54:52.450 --> 54:54.310
"The stories of 'The Lost Flowers'

54:54.510 --> 54:58.480
"are of women whose lives and histories
have been erased,

54:58.680 --> 55:01.030
"mainly by men.

55:01.230 --> 55:05.450
"Men who will never be made
accountable for what they've done

55:05.650 --> 55:09.540
"because they are our sons,

55:09.740 --> 55:13.330
"they are our brothers, our fathers,

55:13.530 --> 55:17.690
"our lovers, our heroes.

55:28.360 --> 55:31.060
"To speak out against them,

55:31.260 --> 55:35.480
"people who we love, that we trust,

55:35.680 --> 55:37.770
"who live in our homes,

55:37.970 --> 55:40.440
"who should be there to protect us,

55:40.640 --> 55:45.780
"to tell those stories
and be heard, believed,

55:45.980 --> 55:48.090
"it is so hard."

55:52.930 --> 55:55.370
What did she leave you?

55:55.570 --> 55:57.730
A final job to do.

55:59.020 --> 56:00.560
Are you ready?

56:04.900 --> 56:07.110
[Candy] What's lost is found.

56:13.280 --> 56:15.660
My love will never leave you.

56:22.670 --> 56:24.460
Resurrection.

56:36.060 --> 56:38.560
Have courage, take heart.

56:47.690 --> 56:50.930
[June]
"But we pay for our silence,
Alice.

56:51.130 --> 56:54.390
"The secrets, the shame,

56:54.590 --> 56:56.660
"it eats away at us."

57:01.620 --> 57:02.690
[Twig] Watch your step.

57:02.890 --> 57:06.670
"It lets men like Dylan
get to be the only voice.

57:15.220 --> 57:18.160
"They get to rewrite history,

57:18.360 --> 57:22.600
"erase us, define who we are.

57:50.340 --> 57:55.840
"I found my voice again
by listening to other women's stories.

57:59.100 --> 58:04.690
"Hearing them speak,
I realised I wasn't alone.

58:23.950 --> 58:28.110
"I give you my story, Alice,
to add to yours,

58:28.310 --> 58:30.360
"because you have a voice,

58:30.560 --> 58:33.280
"a great big beautiful voice,

58:33.480 --> 58:37.180
"and now is the time to use it."

58:55.240 --> 58:59.160
♪ ♪
